==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|иҮӘ|иҫӣ|ls=ic}}, hence "nose" + "chisel; knife to mark prisoners" to indicate the concept of criminal, perhaps with a reference to cutting the nose as a form of punishment. Later, [[иҫ ]] was substituted by [[рҰӢӣ]] (> [[зҪӘ]]), originally a net for fishing, due to the similarity of the former character to [[зҡҮ]], which represents the Emperor.

